description:
&lt;p&gt;COME AND JOIN US on our NEW general medical ward with endocrinology beds within Macclesfield District General Hospital? We are located in the famous silk town of Macclesfield, situated within the beautiful surrounding countryside of the Peak District National Park in Cheshire, and within easy reach of Manchester, Liverpool and Staffordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time for us to develop our services and increase our nursing workforce and you could be part of this excellent opportunity to be part of a brand new team. Ward 2 is a general medical ward, caring for patients with a wide range of medical conditions with endocrinology as a speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly, supportive mutli-professional team spirit, working closely with the multi professional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A structured induction programme with shadowing opportunities and on-going supervision and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Funded training for courses such as Immediate Life Support (ILS) and access to continuing professional development (CPD) funding to help manage your own learning and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plans to create a new 12 month Leadership apprenticeship to run alongside the Preceptorship Programme for Newly Qualified staff&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We welcome full time, part time and secondment applications &lt;/strong&gt;from those of you with a genuine interest in joining us. Although relevant post-registration experience in endocrinology would be preferred, don’t let this deter you. A caring, compassionate, patient-centred approach, with the drive and enthusiasm to deliver high standards of care to get it right first time, every time, we will welcome you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: full time and part time hours available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift patterns:shifts will be either early (7:00-15:00), late (13:00-20:00), long day (7:00-20:00) or night shifts (19:30-7:30)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marie Beckwith, Matron MAU/MIS/AAU - marie.beckwith@nhs.net, 01625 661734&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gill Burrows, Ward Manager - gillian.burrows1@nhs.net, 01625 661954&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
